-- 
Singapore Stocks: Cosco, Sembcorp Marine, Singapore Airlines

-- B y   J o n a t h a n   B u r g o s
-- 
2011-08-02T01:18:21Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-02/singapore-stocks-cosco-sembcorp-marine-singapore-airlines.html
Singapore ’s  Straits Times Index (FSSTI) 
slipped 0.7 percent to 3,193.86 as of 9:15 a.m. local time.
Eight stocks declined for each that rose in the index of 30
companies.  Shares on the measure trade at an average 14.8 times
estimated earnings, compared with about 15.6 times at the end of
2010, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  The following shares were among the most active in the
market. Stock symbols are in parentheses after the company name.  Cosco Corp. Singapore Ltd. (COS SP), the shipbuilding unit
of  China ’s biggest shipping company, slumped 9.4 percent to
S$1.535, the most since May 2009. The company said second-
quarter net income fell 53 percent from a year earlier to S$31.9
million ($26.5 million).  Sembcorp Marine Ltd. (SMM)  , the world’s second-biggest
builder of oil platforms, added 0.4 percent to S$5.42. The
company said its Jurong Shipyard unit won contracts valued at
$444 million to build two jack-up drill rigs for a subsidiary of
Noble Corp. The company will release its second-quarter results
today.  Singapore Airlines Ltd. (SIA)  , the world’s second-
largest carrier by market value, dropped 2.2 percent to S$12.83.
UBS AG cut its rating on the stock to “neutral” from “buy,”
saying a recovery in the company’s earnings will likely be slow.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan Burgos in Singapore at 
